WEBVTT

00:04.170 --> 00:08.257
I dragged you out of hell.
I can throw you back in.

00:09.718 --> 00:12.636
You should show me some respect.

00:12.846 --> 00:14.763
[SCREAMS]

00:14.931 --> 00:18.225
In the coming months,
you will have more decisions to make.

00:18.393 --> 00:21.603
SAM: Dean, what was it like?
-What, hell?

00:22.731 --> 00:26.942
I don't know. I must have blacked it out.
I don't remember a damn thing.

00:27.152 --> 00:28.527
[VOICES SCREAM]

00:30.280 --> 00:34.783
-This is Uriel, a specialist.
-Specializing in what?

00:34.951 --> 00:37.703
Both of you,
you need to leave this town immediately.

00:37.871 --> 00:40.289
-Why?
-Because we're about to destroy it.

00:40.957 --> 00:43.542
The only reason you're still alive,
Sam Winchester...

00:43.710 --> 00:45.294
...is because you've been useful.

00:45.462 --> 00:49.089
The moment that ceases to be true,
and I will turn you to dust.

00:49.716 --> 00:52.760
Ask Dean
what he remembers from hell.

00:54.000 --> 01:00.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:07.794 --> 02:08.836
Hello?

02:10.755 --> 02:12.214
Is anybody there?

02:28.898 --> 02:31.650
Um....
Hello, Mrs. Armstrong.

02:32.068 --> 02:33.152
[SCREAMS]

02:42.787 --> 02:44.705
SAM:
It just doesn't make any sense, Dean.

02:44.873 --> 02:48.167
Why would Uriel tell me
you remembered hell?

02:48.334 --> 02:50.502
-Because he's a dick.
-He's still an angel.

02:50.670 --> 02:53.338
Who was ready to level an entire town.
I don't know wh--

02:53.506 --> 02:56.842
-Radical. What else can I get you guys?
-I think we're good.

02:57.010 --> 02:58.051
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

02:58.219 --> 03:01.096
Wanna try a couple of Fryer Bombs
or a Chipotle Chili Chonga?

03:01.306 --> 03:04.057
-No, no, we're still good.
-Okay, awesome.

03:06.895 --> 03:07.936
[SIGHS]

03:08.104 --> 03:11.857
Sam, honestly, I have no idea
why Uriel told you what he did, okay?

03:13.735 --> 03:15.110
Oh.

03:15.945 --> 03:17.738
Right.

03:18.072 --> 03:20.616
-What?
-Okay, fine. Then look me in the eye...

03:20.825 --> 03:24.828
...and tell me you don't remember a thing
from your time down under.

03:27.874 --> 03:30.792
I don't remember a thing
from my time down under.

03:30.960 --> 03:33.045
-I don't remember.
-Dean, I just wanna help.

03:33.213 --> 03:35.380
You know everything I do.
That's all there is.

03:35.548 --> 03:39.134
-Outstanding. Dessert time? Am I right?
-Dude--

03:39.302 --> 03:42.262
Listen, bros, you have got to try
our Ice Cream Extreme.

03:44.057 --> 03:46.600
-It's extreme.
-No extremities, please.

03:46.768 --> 03:48.602
-Just the--
-Check?

03:48.770 --> 03:50.646
-All right, awesome.
-Thanks.

03:53.233 --> 03:55.067
All right,
so where do we go from here?

03:56.236 --> 03:59.154
Not sure.
Looks like it's been pretty quiet lately.

03:59.322 --> 04:02.658
No signs of demon activity,
no omens or portents I can see.

04:02.867 --> 04:04.952
-That's good news for once.
-Yeah.

04:05.119 --> 04:07.621
Just the typical smattering
of crank UFO sightings...

04:07.789 --> 04:12.251
...and one possible vengeful spirit.
Here, check this out.

04:12.418 --> 04:15.587
Up in Concrete, Washington,
eyewitness reports of a ghost...

04:15.755 --> 04:19.091
...that's been haunting the showers
of a women's health facility.

04:19.259 --> 04:23.095
The victim claims that the ghost
threw her down a flight of stairs.

04:23.846 --> 04:27.516
-I can see you're very interested.
-Women, showers....

04:27.976 --> 04:30.143
We gotta save these people.

04:53.042 --> 04:54.710
[BELL JINGLES]

04:55.503 --> 04:58.797
WOMAN: Oh, Wes, you're the best.
You know I love it here.

04:58.965 --> 05:02.175
-Yeah.
-Oh, I wanna touch you.

05:02.343 --> 05:05.804
I'm not surprised the spirit world
chose to make contact with me.

05:05.972 --> 05:09.141
I'm something of a natural sensitive.

05:10.727 --> 05:15.063
I can sense that about you, Candace.
That whole sensitive thing.

05:16.899 --> 05:18.859
So, what did you say
you're calling your book?

05:19.027 --> 05:23.864
Oh. Well, um,
the working title is Supernatural.

05:24.532 --> 05:27.075
I've been crossing the country
gathering stories.

05:27.243 --> 05:30.037
But anyways, you were telling me
about your encounter.

05:30.204 --> 05:33.749
-Yes, well, once I saw the apparition...
WOMAN: Ha-ha-ha.

05:33.916 --> 05:36.001
...that's when I started to run.

05:36.169 --> 05:38.253
[COUPLE MOANING]

05:45.386 --> 05:50.432
-And you said the ghost chased you?
-Not just that, it knew my name.

05:51.559 --> 05:55.437
It kept yelling,
"Mrs. Armstrong, Mrs. Armstrong!"

05:55.605 --> 05:59.399
-And that's when I hit the stairs and fell.
-You fell?

05:59.567 --> 06:03.403
-The ghost didn't push you?
-Oh, I don't-- I don't know.

06:03.571 --> 06:06.948
I mean, I think it did. Maybe.

06:07.116 --> 06:10.243
Did you feel like it meant to hurt you,
like it was violent or--?

06:10.411 --> 06:13.121
It was a ghost. I'm lucky to be alive.

06:13.289 --> 06:16.041
Anyway,
I was at the bottom of the stairs...

06:16.209 --> 06:18.460
...and that's when it got weird.

06:19.712 --> 06:20.754
[CHUCKLES]

06:20.922 --> 06:22.464
It helped me up.

06:24.634 --> 06:27.761
-Say again?
-Yeah, it helped me up.

06:28.262 --> 06:32.307
And it kept saying over and over,
"Please, don't tell my mom."

06:36.020 --> 06:37.813
Yeah, that's weird.

06:45.613 --> 06:48.657
SAM:
Well, you pick up anything?

06:49.075 --> 06:52.494
No EMF in the shower or anywhere else.
This house is clean.

06:52.662 --> 06:55.747
Yeah, I'm not surprised.
I kind of got the feeling back there...

06:55.915 --> 06:58.417
...that crazy pushed Mrs. Armstrong
down the stairs.

06:58.584 --> 07:00.085
I gotta tell you, I'm disappointed.

07:00.253 --> 07:01.920
Phew. You wanted
to save naked women.

07:02.088 --> 07:03.755
Damn right,
I wanted to save naked women.

07:03.923 --> 07:05.298
[CHUCKLES]

07:05.508 --> 07:09.136
-Come on, guys, get him!
BOY: I got him. I got him.

07:09.303 --> 07:12.681
Run, Forrest, run!

07:12.974 --> 07:15.475
Sorry, Dean,
I don't think anything's going on here.

07:15.643 --> 07:18.854
MAN: How was I supposed to get
a look at it? It grabbed me from behind--

07:19.021 --> 07:21.189
Something's going on.

07:21.357 --> 07:23.984
I understand you got shook up,
anyone would be.

07:24.152 --> 07:27.154
But don't you think it--?
Don't you think it had to be a bear?

07:27.321 --> 07:29.656
I know a damn bear track
when I see one.

07:29.824 --> 07:31.616
This thing didn't leave bear tracks.

07:31.784 --> 07:33.285
-Its feet were huge.
-Now, Gus--

07:33.453 --> 07:37.038
-It was Bigfoot, Hal, the Bigfoot.
-Gus, you're not talking sense here--

07:37.206 --> 07:40.333
There's a Bigfoot out there, damn it,
and he's a son of a bitch!

07:40.501 --> 07:43.170
-Excuse us. FBI.
-What?

07:43.337 --> 07:47.215
-Yes, sir. We're here about the.... That.
-About Bigfoot?

07:47.383 --> 07:51.219
That's right. Sir, can you tell me exactly
where this happened?

07:52.346 --> 07:53.388
Yes, I can.

07:56.476 --> 07:58.894
What the hell's going on in this town?

07:59.061 --> 08:02.189
First there's a ghost that's not real
and now a Bigfoot sighting?

08:02.356 --> 08:05.066
Well, every hunter worth his salt
knows Bigfoot's a hoax.

08:05.234 --> 08:09.070
Yeah, maybe somebody's pumping LSD
into the town water supply.

08:17.622 --> 08:21.750
Okay,
what do you suppose made that?

08:22.919 --> 08:27.255
That, uh, is a big foot.

08:53.574 --> 08:54.950
Okay.

09:03.084 --> 09:07.796
So what, Bigfoot breaks into
a liquor store jonesing for some hooch?

09:09.423 --> 09:13.885
Amaretto and Irish cream.
He's a girl-drink drunk.

09:20.810 --> 09:23.895
Hey, check this out.

09:27.692 --> 09:30.277
He took the whole porno rack?

09:35.491 --> 09:38.618
Well, I'll say it again.
What the hell is going on in this town?

09:59.098 --> 10:00.974
I got nothing.

10:02.518 --> 10:04.853
It's got to be a joke, right?

10:05.021 --> 10:10.942
-Some big-ass mother in a gorilla suit?
-Or it's a Bigfoot.

10:11.110 --> 10:16.948
You know, and he's some kind of
a alcoholo-porno addict.

10:17.116 --> 10:19.868
Kind of like a deep-woods Duchovny.

10:38.679 --> 10:41.514
A little young
for Busty Asian Beauties.

11:17.760 --> 11:20.762
What is this,
like a Harry and the Hendersons deal?

11:22.014 --> 11:23.431
SAM:
Mm.

11:25.768 --> 11:27.769
[KNOCKING]

11:30.314 --> 11:31.940
-Hello?
SAM: Hello.

11:32.108 --> 11:34.275
Um.... Could we--?

11:34.443 --> 11:37.028
-You know what, are your parents home?
-Nope.

11:37.196 --> 11:39.114
-No.
-No.

11:39.281 --> 11:40.615
Um....

11:40.825 --> 11:45.370
-Have you seen a really, really furry--?
-Is he in trouble?

11:47.456 --> 11:51.459
No, no, no. Not at all. We just--

11:51.627 --> 11:54.295
-We wanted to make sure he was okay.
-Exactly.

11:54.463 --> 11:56.131
He's my teddy bear.

11:56.340 --> 11:58.466
[WHISPERS]
I think he's sick.

12:00.553 --> 12:02.470
Wow. Uh....

12:02.638 --> 12:05.306
Amazing, because you know what?

12:05.474 --> 12:11.646
We are, uh, ahem-- Teddy bear doctors.

12:11.856 --> 12:15.442
Really? Can you please
take a look at him?

12:15.609 --> 12:17.485
-Sure, yeah.
-Sure.

12:17.653 --> 12:19.279
Thanks.

12:27.496 --> 12:31.416
He's in my bedroom.
He's pretty grumpy.

12:34.003 --> 12:38.923
Teddy? There's some nice doctors here
to see you.

12:39.091 --> 12:41.760
WOMAN [OVER TV]: --a coalmine
in southeast Ohio collapsed today...

12:41.927 --> 12:44.888
-...killing two people--
-Close the frigging door!

12:48.184 --> 12:49.517
See what I mean?

12:57.318 --> 13:00.904
All I ever wanted was a teddy
which was big, real, and talked.

13:01.071 --> 13:03.198
But now he's sad all the time--

13:03.365 --> 13:05.658
Not "ouch" sad,
but "ouch in the head" sad.

13:06.076 --> 13:08.870
--says weird stuff,
and smells like the bus.

13:10.915 --> 13:13.792
-Um, little girl--
-Audrey.

13:14.293 --> 13:16.169
Audrey.

13:16.337 --> 13:18.546
How exactly
did your teddy become real?

13:18.714 --> 13:19.923
I wished for it.

13:20.090 --> 13:22.217
-You wished for it?
-At the wishing well.

13:25.888 --> 13:28.181
MAN: --meanwhile,
the painstaking search continues--

13:28.349 --> 13:29.516
TEDDY:
Look at this.

13:29.683 --> 13:32.060
--series of explosions
leveled the shopping area--

13:32.228 --> 13:34.854
TEDDY:
You believe this crap?

13:35.147 --> 13:39.108
-Not really.
-It is a terrible world.

13:39.276 --> 13:43.655
-Why am I here?
-For tea parties.

13:43.823 --> 13:46.908
TEDDY:
Tea parties? Ah-ha.

13:47.201 --> 13:49.536
Is that all there is?

13:49.703 --> 13:51.329
[TEDDY SOBBING]

13:51.580 --> 13:54.457
A transatlantic flight
from Dallas to Louisville, Kentucky...

13:54.625 --> 13:56.793
...made an unscheduled landing--

14:00.464 --> 14:02.298
-Audrey, give us a second, okay?
-Okay.

14:02.466 --> 14:03.967
Okay.

14:09.223 --> 14:10.974
Are we--?

14:11.141 --> 14:13.476
Should we--? Uh--

14:13.936 --> 14:15.603
[WHISPERING]
Are we gonna kill this teddy bear?

14:15.771 --> 14:17.564
How, huh? We shoot it, burn it?

14:17.731 --> 14:21.609
-I don't know. Both?
-How do we know that's gonna work?

14:21.777 --> 14:24.946
I don't want some giant, flaming,
pissed-off teddy on our hands.

14:25.114 --> 14:27.532
Yeah. Besides, I get the feeling...

14:27.700 --> 14:31.661
...that the bear isn't really
the, you know, core problem here.

14:31.829 --> 14:34.831
Audrey, where are your parents?

14:34.999 --> 14:39.794
My mom wished they were in Bali,
so I think they're in Bali.

14:41.380 --> 14:42.672
Okay, well--

14:42.840 --> 14:47.135
I'm really sorry to have to break this
to you, but your bear is sick.

14:47.303 --> 14:49.470
Yeah, he's got....

14:50.806 --> 14:52.682
-Lollipop disease.
-Lollipop disease.

14:52.850 --> 14:56.477
It's not uncommon for a bear his size.
But see, it's really contagious.

14:56.645 --> 14:58.855
Yeah, is there someone,
maybe a grownup...

14:59.023 --> 15:01.190
...that you can stay with
while we treat him?

15:01.358 --> 15:04.402
-Mrs. Hurley lives down the street.
-Perfect.

15:04.570 --> 15:07.488
Yeah, good. We'd like you to stay there
for a few days, okay?

15:07.656 --> 15:10.491
-Okay.
-Oh, and Audrey...

15:10.659 --> 15:12.702
...where is this wishing well?

15:27.843 --> 15:28.885
Think it works?

15:29.053 --> 15:31.804
You got a better explanation
for teddy back there?

15:32.556 --> 15:34.891
There's one way to find out.

15:35.184 --> 15:36.809
-What are you gonna wish for?
-Shh.

15:36.977 --> 15:38.019
[COIN FALLS]

15:38.187 --> 15:39.979
You're not supposed to tell.

15:40.606 --> 15:42.023
[CHUCKLES]

15:43.692 --> 15:48.071
Somebody order a foot-long Italian
with jalapeño?

15:49.740 --> 15:51.699
That'd be me.

15:53.035 --> 15:55.203
[COUPLE LAUGHING]

15:56.205 --> 15:59.999
I think it works, dude.
I was pretty specific.

16:00.209 --> 16:02.877
-The teddy bear, the sandwich....
-Hmm.

16:05.214 --> 16:08.549
-I'm guessing this.
-I'm guessing that.

16:08.717 --> 16:11.219
WOMAN:
Ooh. Ha-ha-ha.

16:11.387 --> 16:13.846
Oh, that definitely goes on the list.

16:14.765 --> 16:18.226
What are we supposed to do?
Stop people's wishes from coming true?

16:18.394 --> 16:20.812
-Sounds like a douchey thing to do.
-Yeah, maybe.

16:20.980 --> 16:23.982
But when has something like this
ever come without a price tag?

16:24.149 --> 16:26.859
-And usually a deadly one.
-Oh. I don't know...

16:27.027 --> 16:29.278
...it's a damn good sandwich.

16:31.740 --> 16:34.534
All right, fine.
We'll put a hold on the wishing...

16:34.743 --> 16:37.662
-...until we figure out what's what.
-Gentlemen, I'm sorry.

16:37.830 --> 16:41.749
We don't allow people
to eat outside food here.

16:42.835 --> 16:47.547
Well, I am certainly not
gonna eat the inside food here.

16:47.756 --> 16:49.007
Heh.

16:54.763 --> 16:56.180
[DEAN CLEARS THROAT]

16:56.765 --> 17:01.561
Health department.
You, my friend, have a rat infestation.

17:01.770 --> 17:06.898
We have got to shut this place down
under Emergency Hazard Code 56C.

17:07.067 --> 17:08.776
Rats?

17:12.281 --> 17:15.324
It's a typical fountain, plaster Buddha.
Nothing I can see.

17:15.492 --> 17:19.078
Yes, nothing.
We keep a clean place here.

17:19.288 --> 17:21.247
Sir, I'm gonna have to ask you
to leave...

17:21.415 --> 17:24.459
...during the preliminary investigation.
Okay? Thank you.

17:29.381 --> 17:33.051
Oh, come on,
aren't you a little bit tempted?

17:33.802 --> 17:37.722
Heh-heh. No, wouldn't be real.
Wouldn't trust it.

17:37.890 --> 17:41.309
-I don't know, that bear seemed real.
-Yeah.

17:41.477 --> 17:44.729
Come on, if you could
wish yourself back, before it all started.

17:44.897 --> 17:47.065
Think about it,
you'd be some yuppie lawyer...

17:47.232 --> 17:51.069
-...with a nice car, a white picket fence.
-Not what I'd wish for.

17:51.236 --> 17:53.071
Seriously?

17:53.238 --> 17:56.365
It's too late to go back
to our old lives, Dean.

17:56.533 --> 17:58.534
I mean, I'm not that guy anymore.

17:59.870 --> 18:00.953
[SIGHS]

18:01.121 --> 18:04.040
All right, well, what then? Hmm?
What would Sammy wish for?

18:06.126 --> 18:10.254
Lilith's head on a plate. Bloody.

18:13.717 --> 18:15.635
Okay.

18:18.097 --> 18:20.139
What is that?

18:23.644 --> 18:26.562
Some kind of old coin.
I don't recognize the markings.

18:26.855 --> 18:29.690
DEAN: Ahh. Damn.
-Lift with your legs.

18:33.779 --> 18:36.906
Gah! What, is that little mother
welded on there?

18:39.368 --> 18:40.660
[BELL JINGLES]

18:50.921 --> 18:53.798
Hey, what is this?
You are gonna break my fountain.

18:53.966 --> 18:57.468
Now, sir, I don't wanna slap you
with a 44-slash-16, but I will.

19:02.391 --> 19:04.433
All right, thanks.

19:09.481 --> 19:12.191
Let me see that. I got an idea.

19:24.705 --> 19:26.164
Oh!

19:28.834 --> 19:29.917
DEAN:
Damn.

19:30.502 --> 19:32.503
-Coin's magical.
-Boy, I'd say.

19:35.132 --> 19:37.925
I think it's Hoodoo
that's protecting the well.

19:38.594 --> 19:40.469
I don't think we can destroy this.

19:44.933 --> 19:48.352
-All right, here. You gotta look into this.
-Where are you going?

19:48.937 --> 19:50.521
Something just occurred to me.

19:55.652 --> 19:57.820
[BELL JINGLES]

20:16.089 --> 20:17.465
-What?
-Don't worry, ma'am.

20:17.966 --> 20:20.134
I'm with the Health department.

20:22.638 --> 20:24.889
Ahem.
So you can turn it on and off?

20:25.057 --> 20:26.098
How'd you know I was--?

20:26.266 --> 20:28.809
You walked up to a wishing well,
dropped a dime...

20:28.977 --> 20:32.438
...and wished to be invisible so you
could spy on women in the shower.

20:32.606 --> 20:37.401
[STAMMERING]
No. No. That's crazy.

20:37.694 --> 20:38.819
Put on some pants.

20:40.906 --> 20:44.283
-And stay visible.
-Ow.

20:47.204 --> 20:49.121
O-- Okay.

20:55.379 --> 20:56.879
[BOYS PANTING]

20:57.047 --> 20:58.089
BOY 1:
Hurry up.

21:00.717 --> 21:04.303
BOY 2: Go.
-You better run!

21:08.433 --> 21:12.395
-You got a problem, mister?
-What? No.

21:18.860 --> 21:20.403
[STOMACH GROWLING]

21:20.570 --> 21:22.154
[GRUNTS]

21:23.323 --> 21:24.824
[GRUNTS]

21:29.246 --> 21:31.205
[DEAN VOMITING]

21:31.373 --> 21:32.540
Dean?

21:32.708 --> 21:34.917
[DEAN COUGHS, WATER RUNS]

21:36.670 --> 21:38.587
You all right?

21:39.589 --> 21:44.135
DEAN: The wishes turn bad, Sam.
The wishes turn very bad.

21:44.303 --> 21:47.596
Huh. The sandwich, huh?

21:47.848 --> 21:50.182
[TOILET FLUSHING]

21:51.977 --> 21:53.561
[EXHALES]

21:54.646 --> 21:58.316
The coin is Babylonian. It's cursed.

21:58.483 --> 22:00.818
I found some fragments of a legend,
but--

22:00.986 --> 22:03.487
[GAGS]

22:03.822 --> 22:05.197
Oh....

22:06.074 --> 22:07.867
I'm good.

22:09.661 --> 22:11.120
[DEAN COUGHS]

22:11.580 --> 22:15.082
The serpent is Tiamat...

22:15.250 --> 22:20.504
...which is the Babylonian god
of primordial chaos.

22:22.382 --> 22:23.632
[COUGHS]

22:23.800 --> 22:27.678
I guess her priests
were working some serious Black Magic.

22:27.846 --> 22:31.140
-They made the coin?
-Yeah, to sow the seeds of chaos.

22:31.683 --> 22:35.895
Whoever tosses a coin in a wishing well,
makes a wish, it turns on the well.

22:36.104 --> 22:38.230
Then it starts granting wishes
to all comers.

22:38.398 --> 22:41.233
But the wishes get twisted.
You ask for a talking teddy--

22:41.401 --> 22:44.487
-You get a bipolar nut job.
-And you get E. coli.

22:45.697 --> 22:48.324
This thing has turned
more than one town upside down.

22:48.492 --> 22:50.576
It's even wiped a few off the map.

22:50.744 --> 22:54.246
One person gets their wish, it's trouble.
But everybody gets their wish--

22:54.414 --> 22:56.207
-It's chaos.
-Mm-hm.

22:56.375 --> 22:59.460
-Any way to stop it?
-One way.

22:59.628 --> 23:03.672
We gotta find the first wisher. Whoever
dropped the coin in and made the wish...

23:03.840 --> 23:07.551
...they're the only ones who can
pull it back out and reverse the wishes.

23:07.719 --> 23:11.680
So for now, we've got, you know,
a couple of nutso dreams come true...

23:11.848 --> 23:14.225
...but once the word gets out
about the well...

23:14.393 --> 23:16.352
...things are just gonna get crazier.

23:16.520 --> 23:18.646
[TEDDY SOBBING]

23:34.329 --> 23:36.205
[GUNSHOT]

23:48.176 --> 23:51.846
[SCREAMS]
Why?

24:02.566 --> 24:04.191
[GASPING]

24:07.028 --> 24:11.866
SAM: Dean, wake up.
-What? I'm up. What?

24:12.993 --> 24:15.035
SAM:
You sleep well?

24:21.710 --> 24:24.211
Tanned, rested, and ready.

24:25.797 --> 24:28.924
Dean, come on, man.
You think I can't see it?

24:30.719 --> 24:32.553
See what?

24:32.804 --> 24:34.221
The nightmares, the drinking.

24:34.389 --> 24:37.641
I'm with you 24/7.
I know something's going on.

24:38.226 --> 24:42.438
-Sam, please.
-Uriel wasn't lying, but you are.

24:44.816 --> 24:47.276
You remember hell, don't you?

24:47.736 --> 24:50.738
-What do you want from me? What?
-The truth, Dean.

24:50.906 --> 24:54.408
I mean, I'm your brother.
I just wish you'd talk to me.

24:55.285 --> 24:58.662
-Careful what you wish for.
-Cute.

25:00.582 --> 25:03.292
Come on, can we stow
the couples therapy? We're on a job.

25:03.460 --> 25:06.086
I wanna work. What do you got?

25:06.755 --> 25:08.672
Please?

25:10.592 --> 25:14.929
We got teddy bear, lottery guy,
invisible pervert guy.

25:15.096 --> 25:17.765
They all must have wished
sometime in the last two weeks.

25:17.933 --> 25:18.974
But who wished first?

25:19.142 --> 25:22.603
And how are we supposed to know
who else wished for what, when?

25:24.773 --> 25:28.192
Well, it helps when they announce it
in the paper.

25:31.863 --> 25:34.031
Goes back a month.

25:34.199 --> 25:36.200
"Wesley Mondale
and Ms. Hope Lynn Casey...

25:36.368 --> 25:38.452
...have announced
their surprise engagement."

25:38.620 --> 25:40.871
Ah. True love.

25:41.081 --> 25:43.123
Best lead we got.

25:43.291 --> 25:45.376
[MUSIC PLAYING OVER TV]

25:54.719 --> 25:57.471
-Wes, are you sleeping?
-Hmm?

25:58.306 --> 26:01.976
Oh, uh-- No. No, no, I was just....

26:02.143 --> 26:06.647
-I was just resting my eyes.
-I thought you might want a snack.

26:06.815 --> 26:08.232
Oh. Oh.

26:08.400 --> 26:11.360
-Oh, Hope, you didn't have to do that.
-I wanted to.

26:12.487 --> 26:15.489
Well, no, I....

26:15.657 --> 26:17.575
I had to.

26:17.742 --> 26:20.327
Because I love you more than anything,
lover.

26:22.122 --> 26:24.039
Yes.

26:24.708 --> 26:28.168
-Hope, sit down, okay?
-Yes, Wes.

26:28.503 --> 26:30.170
Um....

26:32.257 --> 26:37.511
-Hope, are you happy?
-I love you more than anything.

26:38.430 --> 26:41.515
I know. I know.

26:41.683 --> 26:43.100
[SIGHS]

26:43.268 --> 26:46.687
And I love you. Very much.

26:48.064 --> 26:52.693
That's why I want you
to start doing things that make--

26:52.861 --> 26:55.195
That made you happy before.

26:56.364 --> 26:59.408
Yes, Wes, I'll try to be happier.
I'll start right away.

26:59.576 --> 27:01.744
No, no, no. That's not what I mean.

27:01.911 --> 27:04.580
Oh, Wes, please.
Please don't be angry with me.

27:04.748 --> 27:06.915
You know, I'd just die, I'd just die.
I'd die.

27:07.083 --> 27:09.376
No, no, no. I'm not angry.
I'm not angry.

27:11.421 --> 27:12.880
Oh.

27:14.174 --> 27:18.385
Then let me make it up to you, Wes.
Let me make it right.

27:18.553 --> 27:19.928
Oh, no, I'm-- I'm--

27:20.305 --> 27:21.388
[ZIPPER OPENS]

27:21.556 --> 27:22.598
[DOORBELL RINGS]

27:22.766 --> 27:24.266
I'll get it.

27:24.893 --> 27:26.393
[ZIPPER CLOSES]

27:27.187 --> 27:29.104
[DOOR OPENS]

27:29.939 --> 27:33.901
Wes, you didn't tell me that
you called the florists for the wedding.

27:34.235 --> 27:37.154
-Huh?
-Oh. You're the best. Mm.

27:37.322 --> 27:38.489
-Wha--?
-Ah!

27:38.698 --> 27:41.909
-I'm gonna go get my folders.
-Okay.

27:42.077 --> 27:44.953
Wesley, how's it going?

27:45.121 --> 27:46.705
It's Wes--

27:47.749 --> 27:49.333
Ss--

27:51.294 --> 27:53.587
-Aren't you from the health department?
SAM: Yeah.

27:53.755 --> 27:56.298
-And florists on the side.
-Plus FBI.

27:56.466 --> 27:59.468
And on Thursdays,
we're teddy-bear doctors.

27:59.636 --> 28:02.638
It doesn't matter who we are.
What matters is what we know.

28:02.806 --> 28:06.016
So a coin collector, huh, Wes?

28:06.476 --> 28:11.772
Oh, yeah.
My grandfather gave them to me.

28:11.940 --> 28:14.983
Did you lose one of those coins lately?
And by "lose," I mean...

28:15.151 --> 28:18.946
...drop into a wishing well
at Lucky Chin's and make a wish on it?

28:19.114 --> 28:23.158
No, I-- I don't know
what you're talking about.

28:23.326 --> 28:27.705
Okay, now. I have a lot of ideas.

28:27.872 --> 28:30.874
But, you know, we don't have
all the money in the world.

28:31.042 --> 28:35.796
Wes is between jobs right now.
Means more time for me.

28:36.798 --> 28:41.260
You know, I'm thinking
a Japanesey-ikebana kind of thing.

28:41.845 --> 28:43.804
-Yes. I can see it.
-Yeah.

28:44.472 --> 28:48.225
So, Hope,
tell us how you two lovebirds met?

28:48.393 --> 28:50.811
-Oh, best day of my life.
-I bet.

28:50.979 --> 28:54.148
Yeah. It's the funniest thing.
We both grew up here...

28:54.315 --> 28:58.318
...but I never really knew who he was.
Not by name anyway.

28:58.653 --> 29:04.032
Oh. Until one day last month,
it was like I just....

29:04.659 --> 29:10.914
I just saw him for the first time.
He was just glowing.

29:11.082 --> 29:13.667
-Just glowing.
-Babe, can you get us some coffee?

29:13.835 --> 29:18.297
-Yes, yeah.
-Oh, okay. Okay.

29:19.424 --> 29:24.219
Mm-hm. Okay. Oh, okay. Mm-hm.

29:24.429 --> 29:26.346
-Okay. Okay.
-Oh.

29:26.514 --> 29:27.556
Okay.

29:27.724 --> 29:32.352
-Okay, okay. Would you--?
-Yeah. Whoa!

29:33.563 --> 29:35.230
[WES CLEARS THROAT]

29:36.357 --> 29:39.067
Wes, we know. So tell us the truth.

29:43.531 --> 29:47.534
WES: My grandfather found the coin
in North Africa...

29:47.702 --> 29:52.539
...you know, World War II,
and he brought it back.

29:52.707 --> 29:59.379
He said it was a real wish-granting coin.
But that nobody should ever use it.

29:59.631 --> 30:01.048
Uh....

30:01.216 --> 30:04.092
He was all I had,
and when he died I thought:

30:04.260 --> 30:07.054
"Well, you know what?
Why not give the coin a shot?"

30:07.722 --> 30:10.641
Yeah, well,
now you're gonna wish it back.

30:10.850 --> 30:12.643
Oh. Heh-heh.

30:14.771 --> 30:16.271
Oh. Ha, ha.

30:16.439 --> 30:18.232
-No, I'm not.
-If you don't stop it...

30:18.399 --> 30:22.361
-...something bad's gonna happen.
-Something bad, like us.

30:26.991 --> 30:29.076
We really wish you'd come with us.

30:34.415 --> 30:38.919
I don't get it. So my wish came true.
Why does that have to be a bad thing?

30:39.087 --> 30:42.756
Because the wishes go south, Wes.
Your town is going insane.

30:42.924 --> 30:45.926
You're gonna tell me
your relationship with Hope is functional?

30:46.094 --> 30:47.594
That it's what you wished for?

30:47.762 --> 30:50.097
I wished she would love me
more than anything.

30:50.265 --> 30:52.808
Yeah, and how is that going?
That seem healthy to you?

30:52.976 --> 30:55.978
Well, it's a lot better
than when she didn't know I was alive.

30:56.145 --> 30:59.273
You're not supposed to get
what you want, man. Not like this.

30:59.691 --> 31:01.483
Nobody is. That's what the coin does.

31:01.651 --> 31:04.486
It takes your heart's desires
and it twists it back on you.

31:04.654 --> 31:07.155
You know the whole,
"be careful what you wish for"?

31:07.323 --> 31:09.283
[THUDDING]

31:10.702 --> 31:13.620
-Did we just hit something?
-I didn't see anything.

31:13.830 --> 31:16.665
[MAN GRUNTS AND GROANS]

31:17.625 --> 31:18.792
Ow.

31:18.960 --> 31:22.838
"Careful what you wish for."
You know who says that?

31:23.006 --> 31:24.798
Good-looking jerks like you guys.

31:24.966 --> 31:28.051
The ones who got it so easy
because you happen to be handsome.

31:28.219 --> 31:29.303
[IN UNISON]
Easy?

31:29.470 --> 31:32.639
Yeah. Women look at you, right?
They notice you.

31:32.807 --> 31:35.809
-Believe us, we do not have it easy.
DEAN: We are miserable.

31:35.977 --> 31:37.311
We never get what we want.

31:37.478 --> 31:40.063
We have to fight
just to keep whatever it is we got.

31:40.231 --> 31:42.024
But maybe that's the whole point.

31:42.191 --> 31:44.693
People are people
because they're miserable bastards.

31:44.861 --> 31:46.653
They never get what they really want.

31:46.821 --> 31:48.906
Right. You get what you want,
you get crazy.

31:49.073 --> 31:52.034
Just take a look at Michael Jackson,
hmm? Or Hasselhoff.

31:53.077 --> 31:56.163
You know what?
Hope loves me now, completely.

31:56.331 --> 31:59.207
And it's awesome.
Besides, look around.

31:59.375 --> 32:01.919
Where's all this insanity
you guys are talking about?

32:02.086 --> 32:04.838
Guy, no-- Just hit the button!

32:05.006 --> 32:06.256
[BOYS YELLING]

32:06.507 --> 32:08.175
-No, don't.
-What's he doing?

32:08.343 --> 32:09.760
Guys! Guys!

32:09.969 --> 32:11.678
[BOYS YELLING]

32:11.846 --> 32:13.722
[ALL SCREAMING]

32:13.973 --> 32:15.515
Well, that should cover it.

32:17.518 --> 32:19.269
BOY 1:
Hold on!

32:21.606 --> 32:24.775
Kneel before Todd!

32:24.984 --> 32:28.028
Kneel before Todd!

32:31.783 --> 32:32.866
[BOYS SCREAMING]

32:33.034 --> 32:35.369
BOY 1: Stop it! Stop it!
BOY 2: Help!

32:37.538 --> 32:40.666
I'll handle Todd.
You get Wes to Lucky Chin's. Go.

32:40.833 --> 32:43.877
-Right.
BOY 3: Oh, my--

32:45.296 --> 32:49.841
-Hey, kid, can I talk to you for a second?
-Get out of my way.

32:50.301 --> 32:53.261
Okay. Hey, I can dig it, Todd.
It's Todd, right?

32:54.305 --> 32:56.890
Look, I know the score, okay?
They're bullying you--

32:57.058 --> 33:00.352
Every day. Every day.
You do not know what it's like.

33:00.520 --> 33:03.897
No. No, I don't. But, you know,
you're you and I'm me, so....

33:04.065 --> 33:07.359
I couldn't stop them.
I couldn't do anything.

33:07.902 --> 33:10.570
Then Audrey Elmer told me
the wishing well worked.

33:11.572 --> 33:16.910
Okay, okay. Look-- Look, I get it.
They're mean little jerks, huh?

33:17.078 --> 33:19.579
But they're not superhuman like you.

33:19.998 --> 33:22.541
You see, with great power
comes great respons--

33:23.084 --> 33:24.584
[GRUNTS]

33:31.384 --> 33:35.679
That-- That kid turned over that car
like it was nothing.

33:35.847 --> 33:37.389
Should have seen the teddy bear.

33:37.557 --> 33:40.350
Now, come on. Fun's over.
Time to pull the coin.

33:40.893 --> 33:44.354
-Wes.
-Why can't we just get what we want?

33:44.522 --> 33:46.189
Because that's life, Wes.

33:47.066 --> 33:48.567
[SAM GRUNTS]

33:57.785 --> 33:59.286
[BELL JINGLES]

34:06.753 --> 34:08.378
Hope?

34:10.630 --> 34:12.466
I had to do it, didn't I?

34:12.632 --> 34:15.217
He was gonna make you
wish away our love.

34:17.597 --> 34:19.056
[GRUNTS]

34:19.389 --> 34:20.974
Oh.

34:22.268 --> 34:23.643
Hah.

34:27.482 --> 34:29.440
Hey, kid.

34:31.319 --> 34:33.487
I didn't wanna have to do this.

34:35.322 --> 34:36.947
Oh!

34:40.244 --> 34:42.161
You wished a man dead?

34:42.371 --> 34:45.791
-I love you more than anything.
-Stop saying that. Stop it.

34:45.958 --> 34:48.793
But I do. More than anything.

34:49.754 --> 34:53.422
More than me. More than life.

34:53.591 --> 34:57.094
Oh, Wes. Don't hate me.

35:03.017 --> 35:06.895
It'll be okay. I'll make it okay.

35:08.356 --> 35:09.981
It'll be okay.

35:14.195 --> 35:16.321
[RUMBLING]

35:16.697 --> 35:18.532
[GRUNTING]

35:29.293 --> 35:31.211
[GASPS THEN COUGHS]

35:40.805 --> 35:44.975
[BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY]

35:45.143 --> 35:49.646
Okay. Follow my lead
and you won't have a problem.

35:49.814 --> 35:51.398
Come on.

35:52.942 --> 35:56.444
Okay, man, no more. No more, okay?

35:57.572 --> 36:00.866
I wouldn't mess with this kid any more
if I were you.

36:04.453 --> 36:06.496
Stay back.

36:18.509 --> 36:20.177
Hope?

36:22.889 --> 36:24.222
Do I know you?

36:38.196 --> 36:39.946
[BELL JINGLES]

36:48.998 --> 36:50.582
[BELL JINGLES]

37:44.679 --> 37:50.433
Well, the coin's melted down.
It shouldn't cause any more problems.

37:50.601 --> 37:54.688
Audrey's parents are back from Bali.
Looks like all the wishes are gone.

37:54.855 --> 37:57.107
And so are we.

38:00.027 --> 38:01.194
[EXHALES]

38:01.362 --> 38:04.197
-Hang on a second.
-What?

38:07.326 --> 38:08.827
You were right.

38:11.205 --> 38:13.123
About what?

38:13.457 --> 38:15.292
I shouldn't have lied to you.

38:17.545 --> 38:21.131
I do remember everything
that happened to me in the pit.

38:22.675 --> 38:24.634
Everything.

38:29.473 --> 38:31.308
So tell me about it.

38:32.310 --> 38:33.810
No.

38:35.730 --> 38:40.400
I won't lie anymore.
But I'm not gonna talk about it.

38:43.237 --> 38:47.324
Dean, look, you can't just shoulder
this thing alone. You gotta let me help.

38:47.700 --> 38:48.825
How?

38:49.535 --> 38:51.244
You think a little heart-to-heart...

38:51.412 --> 38:54.998
...and some sharing and caring
is gonna change anything? Huh?

38:55.166 --> 38:57.584
And somehow heal me?

38:59.378 --> 39:02.422
I'm not talking about a bad day here.

39:02.631 --> 39:03.757
I know that.

39:03.924 --> 39:06.259
The things that I saw....

39:08.179 --> 39:10.430
There aren't words.

39:12.224 --> 39:17.437
There is no forgetting.
There's no making it better.

39:19.774 --> 39:24.944
Because it is right here, forever.

39:29.367 --> 39:31.534
You wouldn't understand.

39:32.536 --> 39:35.705
And I could never
make you understand.

39:36.540 --> 39:38.875
So I am sorry.

40:30.511 --> 40:32.512
[ENGLISH SDH]

